---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const TRADER_NAME = 'J. Wright';
const TRADER_ADDRESS = 'Unit 166847, PO Box 7169, Poole BH15 9EL';
const LAUNCH_DATE = '2026-05-27';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Sale | OddlyWiredCo"
  description="Terms governing the sale of OddlyWiredCo journals, mugs and stickers. Trader identification, delivery, made-to-order goods, and consumer rights under UK law."
>
  <section class="fold light">
    <div class="container legal">
      <p class="meta">Legal · Terms of Sale</p>
      <h1 class="h-mono lg">Terms of Sale</h1>
      <p class="effective">Effective {LAUNCH_DATE}. Last updated {LAUNCH_DATE}.</p>

      <h2>1. About the trader</h2>
      <p>
        These terms apply to all purchases made through oddlywiredco.com (the "Site").
        The trader is {TRADER_NAME} (sole trader), trading as <strong>OddlyWiredCo</strong>,
        at {TRADER_ADDRESS}, United Kingdom. Contact: <a href="mailto:hello@oddlywiredco.com">hello@oddlywiredco.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Contract formation</h2>
      <p>
        When you place an order through the Site you make an offer to purchase the goods at the
        prices shown. Your order is accepted, and a binding contract formed, when we send the
        payment confirmation email from Stripe.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Prices and payment</h2>
      <p>
        All prices are in pounds sterling (GBP) and include UK VAT where applicable. Shipping is
        calculated at checkout based on destination. Payment is processed by Stripe Payments Europe Ltd;
        we do not store your card details. Available payment methods are shown at checkout.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Made-to-order goods</h2>
      <p>
        Our journals, mugs and stickers are produced on demand by our print partner (Printify) once
        your order is confirmed. Each item is made specifically for you. Production typically takes
        2&nbsp;to&nbsp;5 working days before dispatch.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Delivery</h2>
      <p>
        We dispatch from UK and EU print facilities. Estimated total delivery times from order
        confirmation:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>United Kingdom: 5–10 working days</li>
        <li>European Union: 10–15 working days</li>
        <li>Rest of world: 15–25 working days</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Risk in the goods passes to you on delivery. Title passes on payment. For full delivery
        terms see our <a href="/legal/shipping">shipping policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cancellation rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the <em>Consumer Contracts (Information, Cancellation and Additional Charges) Regulations 2013</em>,
        Regulation 28(1)(b), goods that are made to the consumer's specifications or are clearly
        personalised are exempt from the 14‑day right to cancel. Because every OddlyWiredCo item is
        produced on demand to your order, this exemption applies to all of our products.
      </p>
      <p>
        This <em>does not</em> affect your statutory rights regarding defective, damaged, wrong, or
        undelivered goods — see our <a href="/legal/returns">returns and refunds policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Defective or non-conforming goods</h2>
      <p>
        Under the <em>Consumer Rights Act 2015</em>, goods must be of satisfactory quality, fit for
        purpose and as described. If your order arrives defective, damaged, or is not what you
        ordered, we will replace it or refund you in full. See the
        <a href="/legal/returns">returns policy</a> for how to report a problem.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing in these terms limits our liability for death or personal injury caused by our
        negligence, for fraud, or for any other liability that cannot be excluded by law.
        Subject to that, our total liability for any order is limited to the price paid for
        that order.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the law of England and Wales. The courts of England and Wales
        have non-exclusive jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If something has gone wrong, email <a href="mailto:hello@oddlywiredco.com">hello@oddlywiredco.com</a>
        with your order number and we will respond within 2 working days. You may also use the European
        Commission's Online Dispute Resolution platform at
        <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr" rel="noopener noreferrer">ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="back"><a href="/">← Back to OddlyWiredCo</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; }
  .legal .meta { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal h1 { margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal .effective {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--owc-ink);
  }
  .legal p, .legal li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal ul { margin: 4px 0 12px 24px; }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--owc-ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--owc-pulse);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .legal a:hover { background: var(--owc-pulse); }
  .legal .back {
    margin-top: 48px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
  }
  .legal .back a { border-bottom: none; }
</style>
